  "title": "Appendix-IV-Procedure-for-Student-Code-of-Conduct-Incidents-and-Forms_EN.pdf",
  "document_type": "policy_pdf",
  "content": "# Trang 1\nAPPENDIX IV. PROCEDURE FOR STUDENT CODE OF CONDUCT INCIDENTS \nI. ABBREVIATIONS AND FORMS \nSAM: Student Affairs Management \nSDC: Student Disciplinary Committee \nForm 1 (FRM01): Suspected Misconduct Report Form \nForm 2 (FRM02): Student Misconduct Report Form \n \nRefer to Student Code of Conduct Policy and Procedure \n \nII. GENERAL FLOW FOR STUDENT CODE OF CONDUCT INCIDENTS \nStep \nResponsibility \nWorkflow \nTime \nForm \nDetails \n1 \nFaculty \nmembers, \nuniversity staff, \nstudents \n \n \n \n \nFRM01 \n- Evidence can be soft copy and/or hard \ncopy of the violated actions. Ex: photo, \nvideo, suspended misconduct report, etc. \n- Initial handling: when a misconduct action \nis found and required to take immediate \naction, such as using alcohol, drug, fighting, \nsexual harassement etc. If it is safe to do so, \nthe faculty member, university staff, \nresidential assistants can have initial \nhandling before report the case to report \nchannels. \n2 \nSAM \n \n \nWithin 3 working \ndays since the \nviolation date \n \n- SAM notifies the student via email (and \nthrough an in-person meeting if desired) that \nan offense is under investigation process. \nSkip the email notification if there is no need \nmore investiagation and the sanction is \nalready announced when case happens. \n- Student can request a Hearing at this stage \nif they feel it can support their situation. \nSuspect \nviolations report \nvia email or \nphone call \nInvestiagate/Collect more \nevidence (if any) \nInitial handling \n(if needed)\n\n# Trang 2\nStep \nResponsibility \nWorkflow \nTime \nForm \nDetails \n3 \nSAM \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n- SAM checks whether the student has \npreviously violated Student Code of \nConduct. \n4 \nSAM \n \n \n \n \n \n \nWithin 3 working \ndays since the \nviolation date \n \n- SAM follows up on the case in \nconsultation with other units if needed and \nsuggests the appropriate penalty/sanction \nbased on the set of guidelines determined at \nthe university level. \n- Students may be asked for a meeting with \nthe Committee to explain and self-justify the \nsituation. \n5 \nSAM (Level \n1,2) \nSDC (Level 3, \n4) \n \n \n \n \nWithin 3 working \ndays since the \nviolation date \n \n- SAM determines the resolution and \nsanctions on the case at level 1 and level 2. \n- From level 3 and level 4, SAM shall bring \nthe case to SDC for discussion and making \ndecision. \n- Meeting with students can be required \nduring this stage. \n6 \nSAM \n \n \n \n \nWithin 5 working \ndays since the \nviolation date \n \n- A formal letter is sent out from \nconduct@vinuni.edu.vn and a meeting with \nstudent to inform the decision for level 3 and \nlevel 4. \n- If the decision is a suspension or dismissal, \nthe Committee shall seek the Provost or \nPresident’s approval and students' parents \nwill be informed. \nYes \nConfirm \nThe matter \nis closed \nNo \nDefine the severity of student \nmisconduct \nDetermine resolution \n(learning tasks or sanctions) \nLevel 1 \nLevel 2 \nLevel 3 \nNotify the student of decision \nLevel 4\n\n# Trang 3\nStep \nResponsibility \nWorkflow \nTime \nForm \nDetails \n7 \nStudent \n \n \n \nAppeal within 10 working days after the \ndecision is announced. \n8 \nStudent \n \n \nFRM02 \n \n9 \nSAM \n \n \n \n- All allegations of misconduct and the \noutcomes must be documented and archived \nat SAM Office. \n- The information will be entered into the \nStudent Code of Conduct database. \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \nYes \nAccept \ndecision \nSigned Violation \nReport Form \nNo \nAppeal process \nClose-out and \nRecord Keeping",
