        "rag_text": "Table: Appendix-IV-Procedure-for-Student-Code-of-Conduct-Incidents-and-Forms_EN.pdf page 1\nColumns: | Step | | | Responsibility | | | Workflow | | | Time | | | Form | | | Details | \nRow 1: : 1 | Step: | : | : Faculty\nmembers,\nuniversity staff,\nstudents | Responsibility: | : | : Suspect\nviolations report Initial handling\n(if needed)\nvia email or\nphone call | Workflow: | : | : | Time: | : | : FRM01 | Form: | : | : - Evidence can be soft copy and/or hard\ncopy of the violated actions. Ex: photo,\nvideo, suspended misconduct report, etc.\n- Initial handling: when a misconduct action\nis found and required to take immediate\naction, such as using alcohol, drug, fighting,\nsexual harassement etc. If it is safe to do so,\nthe faculty member, university staff,\nresidential assistants can have initial\nhandling before report the case to report\nchannels. | Details: | : \nRow 2: : 2 | Step: | : | : SAM | Responsibility: | : | : Investiagate/Collect more\nevidence (if any) | Workflow: | : | : Within 3 working\ndays since the\nviolation date | Time: | : | : | Form: | : | : - SAM notifies the student via email (and\nthrough an in-person meeting if desired) that\nan offense is under investigation process.\nSkip the email notification if there is no need\nmore investiagation and the sanction is\nalready announced when case happens.\n- Student can request a Hearing at this stage\nif they feel it can support their situation. | Details: | :",
